sclog: sclog (Slackware logs via GNOME notifications)
sclog:
sclog: SCLog is a little tool for GNOME, released under GPL license,
sclog: thought to simplify the life to whom, like me, has the defect of
sclog: checking Slackware current ChangeLog a bit too often. Once selected
sclog: a timeout and the ChangeLog url, SCLog will periodically check for
sclog: upgrades and, if available, will change the icon shown in the tray
sclog: area with a white exclamation mark inside a red spot.
sclog:
